modules.description: Generates cryptographically secure random values including bytes, integers, and UUIDs using safe entropy sources. Works with primitive types and binary data structures. Used for creating secure tokens, initializing cryptographic keys, and generating unique identifiers.

Generates cryptographically secure random values including bytes, integers, floats, and strings. It produces data structures such as Cstruct.t, bytes, bigarray, and string, and supports creating sequences and lists of random elements. Functions like int8, int32, and string allow direct generation of specific data types for secure randomization needs.
